#Text=Sfax
#Text=Sfax is on the east coast of
#Text=Tunisia , approximately midway on the highway between Tunis and the border with Libya .
#Text=By plane
#Text=Sfax-Thyna Airport ( SFA ) . has two flights per week to/from Paris CDG Airport with Tunisair .
#Text=You can also reach Sfax by internal flights with Sevenair from Djerba , Tozeur , Tunis or with a Libyan Airlines flight from Tripoli .
#Text=By car
#Text=A highway connects Sfax to northern cities like Tunis and Sousse .
#Text=By train
#Text=Train connections are available from the train station in the centre of Sfax to most major Tunisian cities .
#Text=The main station , is located just north of the city centre .
#Text=By bus
#Text=There are two has bus stations in Sfax .
#Text=Soretras , which is the regional bus company , and may not offer A/C buses , is on Rue Commondant Bejaoui , a few blocks past the central market .
#Text=SNTRI Bus station , which offers long distance buses , may be marked incorrectly on some travel guide maps .
#Text=It is not across from the regional bus station , but is roughly 400 m to the south , over the train tracks .
#Text=It is probably best to take a taxi there , especially in the summer ( less than 2 DT from the Medina/Blvd Republique ) .
#Text=The bus station is in the same building as the Tunisair office .
#Text=By boat
#Text=Sfax is the gateway to the Kerkennah Islands , 20 kilometers off the coast .
#Text=Sonotrak has up to eight daily departures .
#Text=The is located on 5 Ave Mohamed Hédi Khefacha .
#Text=Get around
#Text=Public transport is easily available in Sfax .
#Text=Taxis are economical , and getting around in the downtown area should cost less than 2 DT per ride .
#Text=For example , this would include from Bab Bhar ( south of the Medina ) to Sfax Jdiid ( north of the Medina ) , or from the Railway station to Hotel Syphax .
#Text=Buses are rarely used by tourists , since they are irregular , slow and crowded .
#Text=If you are going to a destination on one of the roads that radiate out of the city , a taxi might cost about 3.500 DT to kilometer 8 , for example .
#Text=A bus would only cost 0.510 DT .
#Text=These buses depart from locations around the Medina ( mostly to the north or to the east ) .
#Text=The site www.ecfi-t.com has a useful map of bus routes , and other information about Sfax .
#Text=Transport between cities can be done by train or by louage .
#Text=Trains go south to Gabes for the Ksour district or sites where Star Wars was filmed , or north to El Djem , Sousse or Tunis .
#Text=Trains have 3 classes of travel : 2nd class , 1st class and Confort .
#Text=The last is recommended , especially when the train is crowded , since the inspector will move passengers out of seats where they do n't belong .

#Text=The Confort class is a separate section within one of the 1st class coaches , the smaller section , with about 24 seats . ( Often locals do not realise this , and will sit there until moved on by the inspector , or wiser souls . )
#Text=The louage is a minibus of about 9 passengers .
#Text=The Louage station is located beyond the western end of Avenue Bourguiba , about 1½ km from the railway station ( and so is worth a taxi fare ) .
#Text=The louage driver will wait until the bus is full , which may mean an hour or more at quiet times , or to infrequent destinations .
#Text=A wait for a ride to Tunis , El Djem or Sousse should not take too long , but if you are in a hurry and there is only one or two seats left , offer to pay for an extra seat or two .
#Text=Bus transport between cities is also available .
#Text=See
#Text=Archaeological Museum of Sfax ( Muséé de Sfax ) , 9 Ave Habib Bourguiba ( Ground floor of the city hall ) .
#Text=Hosts an impressive collection of mosaics from the region , in particular the Roman towns of Taparura ( where Sfax now is ) and Thaenae ( now Thyna , 11 km west of Sfax ) .
#Text=3 DT .
#Text=Kasbah ( Southwest corner of the Medina ) .
#Text=The kasbah was a military garrison before and during the French Protectorate ( 1881-1956 ) .

#Text=The French influence ( buildings , etc. ) has been removed and the Kasbah now hosts rooms of displays relating the industry for which Sfax is famous ; construction , metalwork and the famous Bourj and Djenes of Sfax all have their own rooms .
#Text=Additionally there is a display of religious architecture and some documents in another room , with an underground mosque area also worth a visit .
#Text=Definitely a highlight is the view from the top of either of the towers that form part of the Kasbah .
#Text=3 DT .
#Text=Dar Djellouli ( See map for location . ) .
#Text=The Djellouli family has provided Sfax with a number of its governors over the years , particularly during the 1700s and 1800s .
#Text=Dar Djellouli is also referred to as the Governor 's Mansion , and is an example of traditional Medina architecture .
#Text=It is built around a courtyard that is open to the sky , with two floors of balconies on four sides looking down on it .
#Text=The rooms open onto these balconies , and house cultural items from the 1800s and even earlier .
#Text=Costumes from the period can be viewed , as can examples of cooking , calligraphy , embroidery , perfume distillation and furniture .
#Text=3 DT .
#Text=Filming locations for The English Patient , Blacksmith 's Souk ( Souq des Forgerons ) ( inside the Medina , near Bab Jebli ) .
#Text=Inside this souk is where Almasy gave Katherine a silver thimble of saffron .
#Text=It no longer houses the blacksmiths , and has bern remodeled around retail .
#Text=See here for more Tunisian film locations .
#Text=Dar Siala and Maison de la photographie ( Dar Kammoun ) , cultural centres and art galleries
#Text=Do

#Text=Wander around the fascinating Medina ( which has an easily mastered and logical layout ) where life and business go on much as they have for years and where tourists , although welcome , are few and far between .
#Text=Ride to Kerkenna on the ferry , with 8 trips a day costing about 800 millimes each way .
#Text=In Kerkenna , get a taxi to the Hotel Cercina where you can walk the beach , or sit on their patio and enjoy tea looking over the bay .
#Text=Check the times of the ferry 's return , and make sure you get a taxi back in time !
#Text=From the Grand Hotel you an also walk the beach , with your destination , the old Bourj , visible in the distance .
#Text=About 1½ km each way , so give yourselves time to enjoy it .
#Text=The Roman ruins beside the Bourj are opened to public as well .
